cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the development of a framework for building a reference model that captures the common and variable analysis/design practices across different applications in a domain. This involves the use of multi-view models and learning capabilities to improve the quality and reusability of the reference model. This topic is closely related to software engineering (cs.SE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and software systems (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of programming languages (cs.PL) in the implementation of the proposed framework.
